HEADWORD: Creepiness
<hw>Creep"i*ness</hw> <pr>(-⟦icr⟧-n⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
uneasy sensation as of insects creeping on the skin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She felt a curious, uneasy <qex>creepiness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Alexander.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

